Implement the following plan:

# Fullscreen Toggle for Canvas & 3D Preview

## Context
The modular apartment planner has a split model workspace: SVG plan canvas (left) and 3D preview panel (right) in a CSS grid. Users want to be able to maximize either panel to use the full canvas area, then toggle back. Currently there is no expand/maximize functionality.

## Approach
Add a `maximizedPanel` state to EditorProvider (`null | 'canvas' | 'preview'`). When set, the `.modelWorkspace` grid hides the non-maximized panel and the active one takes the full width. Each panel gets a small expand/collapse toggle button.

---

## Step 1: EditorProvider State

**File: `src/app/EditorProvider.jsx`**

- Add `maximizedPanel: null` to initial state in `createInitialEditorState` (line ~217)
- Add reducer case `TOGGLE_MAXIMIZE_PANEL`:
  ```js
  case 'TOGGLE_MAXIMIZE_PANEL':
    return {
      ...state,
      maximizedPanel: state.maximizedPanel === action.panel ? null : action.panel,
    };
  ```
- Expose `maximizedPanel` via `useEditor()` (already happens - it spreads `ctx.state`)

## Step 2: App Layout CSS

**File: `src/app/App.module.css`**

Add modifier classes that override `.modelWorkspace` grid when a panel is maximized:

```css
.canvasMaximized {
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
}

.canvasMaximized .preview {
  display: none;
}

.previewMaximized {
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
}

.previewMaximized .primaryCanvas {
  display: none;
}
```

Note: CSS Modules scopes class names, so we can't use nested `.preview` selectors directly. Instead, add standalone `.previewHidden` and `.primaryCanvasHidden` classes with `display: none`, and apply them conditionally in JSX.

## Step 3: App.jsx Layout Wiring

**File: `src/app/App.jsx`** (EditorShell component, ~line 60-100)

- Read `maximizedPanel` from `useEditor()`
- Apply CSS class on `.modelWorkspace`:
  ```jsx
  <div className={`${styles.modelWorkspace} ${maximizedPanel ? styles.workspaceMaximized : ''}`}>
  ```
- Conditionally hide panels:
  ```jsx
  {maximizedPanel !== 'preview' && (
    <div className={styles.primaryCanvas}><SvgCanvas /></div>
  )}
  {maximizedPanel !== 'canvas' && (
    <div className={styles.preview}>
      <Suspense ...><ThreePreviewPanel ... /></Suspense>
    </div>
  )}
  ```
- The `.workspaceMaximized` class sets `grid-template-columns: 1fr` (single column)

## Step 4: Expand Icon

**File: `src/ui/ToolbarIcons.jsx`**

Add two icons:

```jsx
export function ExpandIcon(props) {
  // arrows pointing outward from center
  return <I {...props}><path d="M4 12V16h4" {...p} /><path d="M16 8V4h-4" {...p} /><path d="M4 16l5-5" {...p} /><path d="M16 4l-5 5" {...p} /></I>;
}

export function CollapseIcon(props) {
  // arrows pointing inward
  return <I {...props}><path d="M9 15v-4H5" {...p} /><path d="M11 5v4h4" {...p} /><path d="M5 15l4-4" {...p} /><path d="M15 5l-4 4" {...p} /></I>;
}
```

## Step 5: SvgCanvas Expand Button

**File: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx`**

Add a small expand/collapse button in the status bar area (bottom-right corner of the canvas container). The button sits inside `.canvasContainer` as an absolutely positioned element.

```jsx
const { maximizedPanel, dispatch: editorDispatch } = useEditor();
const isCanvasMaximized = maximizedPanel === 'canvas';

// Inside the canvasContainer div, add:
<button
  className={styles.expandBtn}
  onClick={() => editorDispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_MAXIMIZE_PANEL', panel: 'canvas' })}
  title={isCanvasMaximized ? 'Restore split view' : 'Maximize canvas'}
  aria-label={isCanvasMaximized ? 'Restore split view' : 'Maximize canvas'}
>
  {isCanvasMaximized ? <CollapseIcon /> : <ExpandIcon />}
</button>
```

**File: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.module.css`**

```css
.expandBtn {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 32px;  /* above status bar */
  right: 8px;
  width: 28px;
  height: 28px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  background: var(--color-surface-elevated);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  cursor: pointer;
  opacity: 0.7;
  transition: opacity var(--duration-fast), background var(--duration-fast);
  z-index: 5;
}

.expandBtn:hover {
  opacity: 1;
  background: white;
}

.expandBtnIcon {
  width: 14px;
  height: 14px;
}
```

## Step 6: ThreePreviewPanel Expand Button

**File: `src/three/viewer/ThreePreviewPanel.jsx`**

- Accept new props: `isMaximized`, `onToggleMaximize`
- Add expand/collapse button in the `.actions` div (next to "Reset View"):
  ```jsx
  <button type="button" className={styles.button} onClick={onToggleMaximize}>
    {isMaximized ? <CollapseIcon /> : <ExpandIcon />}
  </button>
  ```

**File: `src/app/App.jsx`** (where ThreePreviewPanel is rendered):
- Pass props:
  ```jsx
  <ThreePreviewPanel
    project={project}
    activeFloorId={activeFloorId}
    isMaximized={maximizedPanel === 'preview'}
    onToggleMaximize={() => editorDispatch({ type: 'TOGGLE_MAXIMIZE_PANEL', panel: 'preview' })}
  />
  ```

---

## Files Modified
| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `src/app/EditorProvider.jsx` | Add `maximizedPanel` state + `TOGGLE_MAXIMIZE_PANEL` action |
| `src/app/App.module.css` | Add `.workspaceMaximized` class |
| `src/app/App.jsx` | Read `maximizedPanel`, conditionally hide panels, pass props to ThreePreviewPanel |
| `src/ui/ToolbarIcons.jsx` | Add `ExpandIcon` and `CollapseIcon` |
| `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx` | Add expand button in canvas container |
| `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.module.css` | Add `.expandBtn` styles |
| `src/three/viewer/ThreePreviewPanel.jsx` | Add expand button in header actions |

## Verification
1. `npm run dev` - open app in browser
2. In plan view, verify split layout shows SVG canvas + 3D preview side by side
3. Click expand button on SVG canvas -> 3D preview disappears, canvas takes full width
4. Click collapse button -> split view restores
5. Click expand button on 3D preview header -> SVG canvas disappears, preview takes full width
6. Click collapse on preview -> split view restores
7. Switch to elevation/section view -> maximize state persists correctly
8. Switch to sheet workspace -> maximize doesn't apply (sheets have no split)
9. Verify 3D preview ResizeObserver fires correctly when maximizing/restoring (viewport resizes properly)
10. Verify keyboard shortcuts still work in both states


If you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: C:\Users\johnm\.claude\projects\C--Users-johnm-modular-apartment-planner\c091a3bd-13c6-4ca3-9c64-8b758fcb693d.jsonl

